david cole  mk metal products inc  zoominfocom david d cole  wikipedia david d cole from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search for other people named david cole see david cole disambiguation this biography of a living person needs additional citations for verification please help by adding reliable sources contentious material about living persons that is unsourced or poorly sourced must be removed immediately especially if potentially libelous or harmful november  learn how and when to remove this template message david d cole alma mater yale law school occupation national legal director employer american civil liberties union david d cole is the national legal director of the american civil liberties union aclu before joining the aclu in january  cole was the hon george j mitchell professor in law and public policy at the georgetown university law center from march  through december  he has published in various legal fields including constitutional law national security criminal justice civil rights and law and literature cole has litigated several significant first amendment cases in the supreme court of the united states as well a number of influential cases concerning civil rights and national security he is also a legal correspondent to several mainstream media outlets and publications contents  legal career  academic career  media commentary  honors and awards  publications  personal life  references  external links legal careeredit cole graduated magna cum laude from yale college in  and received his juris doctor jd degree from yale law school in  after graduating from law school cole served as a law clerk to judge arlin m adams of the united states court of appeals for the third circuit he then became a staff attorney for the center for constitutional rights where he litigated a number of major first amendment cases including texas v johnson  us   united states v eichman  us   and united states v haggerty consolidated with eichman he later served as a voluntary staff attorney at the center where he also sat on the board of directors from  after leaving the center for constitutional rights david cole began teaching at georgetown university law center while teaching at georgetown law cole continued to litigate constitutional law and civil liberties both at home and abroad during the s cole argued over a dozen cases in various us district and circuit courts and appeared before the supreme court three times lebron v national railroad passenger corporation  us   national endowment for the arts v finley  us   and reno v americanarab antidiscrimination committee  us   internationally cole successfully challenged irelands constitutional prohibition on counseling about abortion before the european court of human rights in open door counselling ltd v republic of ireland echr judgment of october   ser a no  he returned to europe in fall  to teach at the university college london school of public policy and serve as codirector of the center for transnational legal studies in london froom  cole was named cochair of the constitution projects liberty and security committee in  and joined the advisory committee for the free expression policy project in  he has served on boards for a number of public interest organizations including human rights watch advisory committee bill of rights defense committee and the american bar association standing committee on law and national security his most recent appearance before the supreme court was in  challenging the first and fifth amendment implications of the usa patriot acts prohibition on providing material support to terrorist groups in holder v humanitarian law project  us   from  cole was a fellow with the open society foundations an international grantmaking network founded by business magnate george soros that dispenses financial contributions to various liberal and progressive political causes in the united states academic careeredit david cole was a member of the georgetown university law center faculty from  he has also taught at new york university law school and university college londons school of public policy as a visiting scholar as a professor coles main areas of expertise were constitutional law criminal procedure national security and law relating to united states federal courts he gained tenure at georgetown law in  and was selected as the schools inaugural hon george j mitchell professor in law and public policy cole has written eight books for which he has received numerous awards including the palmer civil liberties prize for best book on national security and civil liberties the american book award  and boston book reviews best nonfiction book  his most recent book engines of liberty the power of citizen activists to make constitutional law was named one of the washington posts notable nonfiction books of  in addition to writing cole has also lectured and contributed academic articles on related topics including judicial review domestic drugs policy the war on terror and capital punishmentcitation needed he has been published in law journals nationwide including the yale law journal stanford law review university of chicago law review and california law review he has also written articles for numerous mainstream publications including the new york times washington post the new republic the wall street journal and the los angeles times media commentaryedit cole has been the legal affairs correspondent for the nation since  he is also a commentator on the national public radio program all things considered providing viewpoints from a liberal  progressive perspective and a contributor to the new york review of books he was interviewed in the  bbc documentary the power of nightmares  the rise of the politics of fear honors and awardsedit david cole has received awards from professional bodies and campaigning groups for his civil rights and civil liberties work including from the american bar associations individual rights and responsibilities section the national lawyers guild the americanarab antidiscrimination committee and the american muslim council in  he received the william j brennan award from the thomas jefferson center for the protection of free expression which cited cole as one of the nation’s most accomplished advocates for freedom of expression and an outstanding scholar of the first amendment in  david cole also was the first recipient of the aclus norman dorsen presidential prize for academic contributions to civil liberties publicationsedit cole david november  playing by pornographys rules the regulation of sexual expression university of pennsylvania law review the university of pennsylvania law review   – jstor  doi  cole david  no equal justice race and class in the american criminal justice system new york city the new press isbn  oclc   cole david james x dempsey  terrorism and the constitution sacrificing civil liberties in the name of national security los angeles the new press isbn  oclc   cole david  enemy aliens double standards and constitutional freedoms in the war on terrorism new york city the new press isbn  oclc   cole david january–february  closing guantánamo the problem of preventive detention boston review    cole david  the torture memos rationalizing the unthinkable new york city the new press p  isbn   personal lifeedit cole is married to former georgetown law professor and current dc circuit court of appeals judge nina pillard they have two children sarah and aidan pillard referencesedit  a b david cole aclu job is ‘dream come true’ wwwdcbarorg retrieved    georgetown law faculty david d cole biography and selected publications  mitchell professorship awarded  retrieved    a b c d e f g h profile david cole — georgetown law wwwlawgeorgetownedu retrieved    a b c d warner judith  us border security a reference handbook abcclio p  isbn    aclu taps constitutional expert david cole as national legal director american civil liberties union retrieved    cole david  engines of liberty the power of citizen activists to make constitutional law  ed basic books isbn    david cole the nation retrieved    david cole  the new york review of books nybookscom retrieved    the william j brennan jr award thomas jefferson center for the protection of free expression accessed december    professor david cole to receive aclu foundation award for lifetime commitment to civil liberties — georgetown law lawgeorgetownedu  retrieved    aclu inaugurates dorsen presidential prize to honor outstanding academic contribution to civil liberties aclu news release may   accessed december    georgetown law goes international  the georgetown voicethe georgetown voice georgetownvoicecom  retrieved   external linksedit georgetown law faculty david d cole biography and selected publications center for constitutional rights the nation articles by david d cole ssrn articles by david d cole video david cole  enemy aliens  constitutional freedoms february   cole article archive from the new york review of books authority control worldcat identities viaf  gnd  sudoc  bnf cbb data retrieved from httpsenwikipediaorgwindexphptitledaviddcoleoldid categories american lawyersamerican legal scholarsamerican legal writersliving people birthsyale law school alumnigeorgetown university law center facultythe nation us magazine peoplehidden categories blp articles lacking sources from november all blp articles lacking sourcesarticles with hcardsall articles with unsourced statementsarticles with unsourced statements from december wikipedia articles with viaf identifierswikipedia articles with gnd identifierswikipedia articles with bnf identifiers navigation menu personal tools not logged intalkcontributionscreate accountlog in namespaces article talk variants views read edit view history more search navigation main pagecontentsfeatured contentcurrent eventsrandom articledonate to wikipediawikipedia store interaction helpabout wikipediacommunity por