iminal procedure national security and law relating to united states federal courts he gained tenure at georgetown law in  and was selected as the schools inaugural hon george j mitchell professor in law and public policy cole has written eight books for which he has received numerous awards including the palmer civil liberties prize for best book on national security and civil liberties the american book award  and boston book reviews best nonfiction book  his most recent book engines of liberty the power of citizen activists to make constitutional law was named one of the washington posts notable nonfiction books of  in addition to writing cole has also lectured and contributed academic articles on related topics including judicial review domestic drugs policy the war on terror and capital punishmentcitation needed he has been published in law journals nationwide including the yale law journal stanford law review university of chicago law review and california law review he has also written articles for numerous mainstream publications including the new york times washington post the new republic the wall street journal and the los angeles times media commentaryedit cole has been the legal affairs correspondent for the nation since  he is also a commentator on the national public radio program all things considered providing viewpoints from a liberal  progressive perspective and a contributor to the new york review of books he was interviewed in the  bbc documentary the power of nightmares  the rise of the politics of fear honors and awardsedit david cole has received awards from professional bodies and campaigning groups for his civil rights and civil liberties work including from the american bar associations individual rights and responsibilities section the national lawyers guild the americanarab antidiscrimination committee and the american muslim council in  he received the william j brennan award from the thomas jefferson center for the protection of free expression which cited cole as one of the nation’s most accomplished advocates for freedom of expression and an outstanding scholar of the first amendment in  david cole also was the first recipient of the aclus norman dorsen presidential prize for academic contributions to civil liberties publicationsedit cole david november  playing by pornographys rules the regulation of sexual expression university of pennsylvania law review the university of pennsylvania law review   – jstor  doi  cole david  no equal justice race and class in the american criminal justice system new york city the new press isbn  oclc   cole david james x dempsey  terrorism and the constitution sacrificing civil liberties in the name of national security los angeles the new press isbn  oclc   cole david  enemy aliens double standards and constitutional freedoms in the war on terrorism new york city the new press isbn  oclc   cole david january–february  closing guantánamo the problem of preventive detention boston review    cole david  the torture memos rationalizing the unthinkable new york city the new press p  isbn   personal lifeedit cole is married to former georgetown law professor and current dc circuit court of appeals judge nina pillard they have two children sarah and aidan pillard referencesedit  a b david cole aclu job is ‘dream come true’ wwwdcbarorg retrieved    georgetown law faculty david d cole biography and selected publications  mitchell professorship awarded  retrieved    a b c d e f g h profile david cole — georgetown law wwwlawgeorgetownedu retrieved    a b c d warner judith  us border security a reference handbook abcclio p  isbn    aclu taps constitutional expert david cole as national legal director american civil liberties union retrieved    cole david  engines of liberty the power of citizen activists to make constitutional law  ed basic books isbn    david cole the nation retrieved    david cole  the new york review of books nybookscom retrieved    the william j brenn